## Test Anti-Pattern Audit — Severity-Ranked Findings

This test file is a textbook example of **"coverage theater"** — every production method is called (achieving line coverage) but almost nothing meaningful is asserted.

---

### 🔴 Critical — Assert-Free Tests (Coverage Without Verification)

| # | Test | Bug It Would Miss |
|---|------|-------------------|
| 1 | `AddProduct_Works` (L17-21) | `Save` could silently fail or store wrong data — no assertion at all. |
| 2 | `UpdatePrice_Works` (L33-35) | Price might not change; could save wrong SKU, old price, etc. |
| 3 | `RemoveProduct_Works` (L38-42) | Product could still exist after removal — never checked. |
| 4 | `GetProductCount_Works` (L63-66) | Return value is discarded. Count could be -1 and this passes. |
| 5 | `ApplyBulkDiscount_Works` (L68-74) | Prices might not actually decrease, or discount could be applied backwards. |
| 6 | `ImportFromCsv_Works` (L84-88) | Imported product never verified to exist in the catalog. |

**Fix pattern:** Assert on observable outcomes.

```csharp
// Example fix for UpdatePrice_Works
[TestMethod]
public void UpdatePrice_UpdatesStoredPrice()
{
    _catalog.AddProduct(new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m));
    _catalog.UpdatePrice("SKU-001", 14.99m);
    var updated = _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001");
    Assert.AreEqual(14.99m, updated!.Price);
}
```

---

### 🟠 High — Weak Assertions (IsNotNull on non-nullable paths)

| # | Test | Problem |
|---|------|---------|
| 7 | `GetProduct_Works` (L25-29) | `Assert.IsNotNull` passes even if Name/Price are wrong. Doesn't verify correctness. |
| 8 | `SearchProducts_Works` (L47-52) | Asserts list isn't null but never checks count or content — returns wrong product? Passes. |
| 9 | `GetAllProducts_Works` (L55-60) | Same — empty list or extra items would pass. |
| 10 | `ExportToCsv_Works` (L77-82) | Checks string isn't null but not format, content, or delimiters. |

**Fix pattern:** Assert on value correctness, not just existence.

```csharp
// Example fix for SearchProducts_Works
[TestMethod]
public void Search_ReturnsOnlyMatchingProducts()
{
    _catalog.AddProduct(new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m));
    _catalog.AddProduct(new Product("SKU-002", "Gadget", 19.99m));
    var results = _catalog.Search("Widget");
    Assert.AreEqual(1, results.Count);
    Assert.AreEqual("SKU-001", results[0].Sku);
}
```

