### Summary

| Severity | Count | Root Cause |
|----------|-------|------------|
| 🔴 Critical | 6 | No assertions — "call it and pray" |
| 🟠 High | 4 | `IsNotNull` on things that are structurally never null |
| 🟡 Medium | 5 | Missing negative/boundary cases |

**Root diagnosis:** Every test follows the pattern "arrange, act, **done**" — the Assert step is either absent or trivial (`IsNotNull`). This gives 95% line coverage because every line *executes*, but zero behavioral guarantees. Bugs in price calculation, query filtering, CSV formatting, and deletion logic would all ship green.
